      • getProtobufValue

        public static java.lang.String getProtobufValue(DynamicProtobufContentParser protobufContentParser,
                                int delimitedMessageIndex,
                                java.lang.String protobufKey)
        Get a value as a string from G-PROTOBUF data.
        Parameters:
        protobufContentParser - a valid initialized instance of a G-PROTOBUF parser
        delimitedMessageIndex - index of delimited message (0..n-1) or pass a value of -1 for a single message
        protobufKey - a valid G-PROTOBUF key. Example: "person[0].phone[1].type"
        Returns:
        a value as a string from G-PROTOBUF data. Note: If the data type of the value is a BYTE_STRING then a base64 encoded string is returned.
        See Also:
        DynamicProtobufContentParser.containsDelimitedMessages(), ProtobufFieldAndValueElement

      • getProtobufValueBySearchText

        public static java.lang.String getProtobufValueBySearchText(DynamicProtobufContentParser protobufContentParser,
                                            java.lang.String searchForIndexText,
                                            int indexOffset,
                                            java.lang.String protobufKey)
        Get a value as a string from G-PROTOBUF data by searching a text fragment overall delimited messages.
        NOTE: This method cannot be used for single messages !
        Parameters:
        protobufContentParser - a valid initialized instance of a G-PROTOBUF parser that contains multiple delimited messages
        searchForIndexText - the text fragment to search overall delimited messages. For the first match the message index is determined
        indexOffset - additional offset to the message index, applied after the search text is found (can be a positive or negative number, 0 = current index)
        protobufKey - a valid G-PROTOBUF key. Example: "person[0].phone[1].type"
        Returns:
        a value as a string from G-PROTOBUF data. Note: If the data type of the value is a BYTE_STRING then a base64 encoded string is returned.

      • getProtobufValue

        public static java.lang.String getProtobufValue(DynamicProtobufContentParser protobufContentParser,
                                int delimitedMessageIndex,
                                java.lang.String protobufKey,
                                int tokenNumber,
                                java.lang.String delimiterChars,
                                boolean tokenTrim)
        Get a value as string-token from G-PROTOBUF data.
        Parameters:
        protobufContentParser - a valid initialized instance of a G-PROTOBUF parser
        delimitedMessageIndex - index of delimited message (0..n-1) or pass a value of -1 for a single message
        protobufKey - a valid G-PROTOBUF key. Example: "person[0].phone[1].type"
        tokenNumber - token nr. 1..n, 0 == invalid
        delimiterChars - string tokenizer delimiters
        tokenTrim - true = trim extracted token
        Returns:
        a value as string-token from G-PROTOBUF data, or null if no such token can be extracted
        See Also:
        DynamicProtobufContentParser.containsDelimitedMessages(), ProtobufFieldAndValueElement

      • setStringFieldValueReplacePattern

        public static void setStringFieldValueReplacePattern(DynamicProtobufContentParser protobufContentParser,
                                     int delimitedMessageIndex,
                                     java.lang.String protobufKey,
                                     java.lang.String pattern,
                                     java.lang.String newValue,
                                     int occurrencePosition)
                                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Searches inside a G-PROTOBUF string a text-pattern and replaces this pattern with a new value.
        Parameters:
        protobufContentParser - a valid initialized instance of a G-PROTOBUF parser
        delimitedMessageIndex - index of delimited message (0..n-1) or pass a value of -1 for a single message
        protobufKey - a valid G-PROTOBUF key. Example: "person[0].phone[1].type"
        pattern - the text-pattern which is searched within the string
        newValue - the value which replaces the pattern
        occurrencePosition - the occurrence position of the pattern within the string (1 = first match, 2 = second match ... 0 = replace all patterns)
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
